        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-md-offset-1">
                <div class="pull-right">
                                    <a class="btn btn-success"
           href="add-new-collection-prototype#play">
            Next Chapter <i class="fa fa-caret-right"></i>
        </a>
    
                </div>

                <ul class="nav nav-tabs" role="tablist">
                    <li class="active"><a data-toggle="tab" href="collection-delete-orphan-removal#tab-script">Script</a></li>
                    <li><a data-toggle="tab" href="collection-delete-orphan-removal#tab-comment">
                        <i class="fa fa-comment-o"></i>
                                                    
                                                        Conversation
                                            </a></li>
                </ul>

                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab-script">
                        <div class="js-script-content-wrapper top-margin-script markdown-content">
                                                                                        <a href="https://github.com/knpuniversity/symfony/edit/master/knpu/extra-doctrine-collections/collection-delete-orphan-removal.md" target="_blank" class="btn btn-default btn-circle pull-right js-tooltip" title="Edit on GitHub"><span class="fa fa-pencil"></span></a>
                                                                    <p>When we delete one of the <code>GenusScientist</code> forms and submit, the <code>CollectionType</code>
is now smart enough to <em>remove</em> that <code>GenusScientist</code> from the <code>genusScientists</code>
array on <code>Genus</code>. So, why doesn't that make any difference to the database?</p>
<p>The problem is that the <code>genusScientists</code> property is now the <em>inverse</em> side of
this relationship:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="d2e7be441c">
