<p>But by setting it to false, it's going to give us the flexibility we need to
set the owning side of the relationship.</p>
<h2 id="setting-the-owning-side-adder-amp-remover">Setting the Owning Side: Adder &amp; Remover <a class="headerlink" href="collection-delete-orphan-removal#setting-the-owning-side-adder-amp-remover" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>With <em>just</em> that change, submit the form. Error! But look at it closely: the error
happens when the form system calls <code>removeGenusScientist()</code>. That's perfect! Well,
not the error, but when we set <code>by_reference</code> to false, the form started using our
adder and remover methods. <em>Now</em>, when we delete a <code>GenusScientist</code> form, it calls
<code>removeGenusScientist()</code>:</p>
